                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso)" facs="001 002">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso)</locus><desc>Crude drawings of several figures, some in pencil and some in blue ink</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/>, with seven talismanic faces to the left in boxes</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc>An Ethiopian dignitary (left), holds a large ornate <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1071Cross">Cross</ref>. Another man (right), holds a rifle by the barrel with a hand cross behind him. Above both are two figures, one holding an umbrella for the other and a church in the center background with captions (l. to r.) <q>“Jesus’ Cross,”</q> <q>“The Ark,”</q> <q>“Processional Umbrella (Dǝbab),”</q> <q>“Saviour of the World,”</q> and <q>“rifle.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#87r" facs="089">Fol. 87r</locus><desc>King Herod supervising the scourging of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref> with captions <q>“King Herod,”</q> <q>“Our Lord scourced,”</q> <q>“Jews,”</q> and <q>“Jews.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#88v" facs="091">Fol. 88v</locus>An <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/>, in black ink</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#89r" facs="091">Fol. 89r</locus><desc>Two <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref>s with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/>s and <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/>s, in pencil</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#89v" facs="092">Fol. 89v</locus><desc>Crude drawings of two figures and a bird</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#Back inside cover" facs="092">Fols. Back,, </locus><desc>Crude drawing of two men</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d9">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="003">fols. 1r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                    <locus target="#3v #17v #23r #26r #27r #47r #57v #62v #67r #67v #75v #79r #86r #86v" facs="006 020 025 028 029 049 060 065 069 070 078 081 088 089">3v, 17v, 23r, 26r, 27r, 47r, 57v, 62v, 67r, 67v, 75v, 79r, 86r, 86v, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                    <locus target="#17v #23r #62v #86r" facs="020 025 065 088">17v, 23r, 62v, 86r, </locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#71r" facs="073">71r</locus> (full stops connected with red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
