                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    <locus target="#86r #86v" facs="088 089">Fols. 86r, 86v</locus>
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5888AsmatPrayer">ʾAsmāt-prayer
                                                  (general record)</title> of the Archangel (with a list of names written on his left wing) as a prayer for the owner, Ḫaylä Iyyäsus (<locus target="#70r"> f. 70r and passim</locus>) and his wife Amätä Giyorgis, in Amharic and Gә‘әz
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#86r" facs="088"> f. 86r and passim</locus>
                    Scribe, Wäldä Arägawi
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                    <locus target="#86v" facs="089">Fol. 86v</locus>
                    Record of the purchase of the manuscript by Ato Wärqu Gäbrä Mäsqäl, (baptismal name is Wäldä Ḫawaryat) in 1950 E.C. in the town of Gǝmbi [in Shäwa], in blue ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#87v" facs="090">Fol. 87v</locus>
                    Record of events: “Empress Zäwditu, daughter of Mǝnilǝk, king of kings, died on 24 Miyazya, on the feast day of Täklä Haymanot. King Ḫaylä Śǝllase also was crowned king on the feast day of Kidanä Mǝḫrät and he sat on the throne of Mǝnilǝk in the year of 1922 (E.C. = 1930), in the year of Saint Mark.  My son, Mulugeta, [had a] son, Aläm Ayähu, [who] was born on Gǝnbot 30, 1922 E.C. (= June 7, 1930), in the year of Saint Mark.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                    <locus target="#88r" facs="090">Fol. 88r</locus>
                    Record of other events, including transaction lending salt and birr
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1v #4v #7r #9v" facs="004 007 009 012">folss. 1v, 4v, 7r, 9v, </locus>, etc.);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#7v #30r #38v" facs="010 032 041">7v, 30r, 38v</locus>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
